Quote: The shutting-up technique used at present consists of confining sheep at the rate of 100-200 per acre (250-500 per hectare) or sufficient to eat out the pasture in 24 hours. Fattening lambs should not be shut-up.
Notes: NZ Vets Assn Diseases of Domestic Animals in NZ
